# Architecture

```text
             User
               │
               ▼
          BookScreen
               │
               ▼
        BookViewModel
               │
               ▼
      BookRepository
               │
               ▼
   BookRepositoryImpl
               │
               ▼
        FakeBookApi
               │
               ▼
        Book Data Source
```

---

# Why Use the Repository Pattern?

Without a Repository:

```text
ViewModel
      │
      ▼
FakeBookApi
```

The ViewModel depends directly on the data source.

With a Repository:

```text
ViewModel
      │
      ▼
Repository
      │
      ▼
API / Database / Cache
```

The ViewModel only knows about the Repository, making it easier to replace or combine data sources without changing the ViewModel.

---

# Key Takeaways

* The ViewModel should not access APIs directly.
* A Repository acts as the single source of data for the ViewModel.
* Interfaces make implementations interchangeable.
* Business logic remains separate from UI logic.
* The Repository Pattern improves
